, it quickly became popular because of its simple design, strong durability, and exceptionally long battery life. Unlike modern smartphones, the Nokia 3310 focused mainly on basic communication features such as calling and texting, making it easy and reliable for everyday use. It featured a monochrome screen, a physical keypad, and useful built-in tools like an alarm clock, calculator, and calendar. The phone was also well known for including the classic game Snake II, which became a favorite pastime for many users. Over the years, the Nokia 3310 gained legendary status due to its reputation for being nearly indestructible, and it remains a symbol of early mobile phone technology and reliability.', 2499, NULL, 49, 'Electronics', 'https://static.wikitide.net/lpcwikiwiki/thumb/f/fa/Nokia_3310.jpg/900px-Nokia_3310.jpg', NULL, 5);

